<exercise checkit-seed="0004" checkit-slug="G1" checkit-title="Area">
    <statement>
        <p> A trapezoid is placed with the shorter parallel side on top and a triangle is attached cleanly to the top of the trapezoid. The dimensions of the shape are as follows: the bottom of the trapezoid has length 8, the top of the trapezoid has length 7 and the altitude is 4, while the triangle has height 10, where everything is measured in meters.
            <ol>
                <li>Sketch a drawing of this situation to the best of your ability.</li>
                <li>Find the total area of this shape.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            The volume is <m>A \approx 65.0</m> <m>m^2</m>. This was computed using the formula <me>A = \frac{1}{2}\left(b_1 + b_2\right)h_1 + \frac{1}{2}b_2 h_2</me>.
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
